	        <tr>
			  <td colspan=2 valign="top"><br>
		          <span class=msg>
                   After months of enjoying free reign at the office, our landlord's new tech has started blocking ports.  Consequently, this means I can't patch or connect to the game anymore from work.  Our IT guy doesn't have any problem with EQ connections, but the landlord's tech is being paranoid after getting portscanned, and is blocking all inbound and outbound ports other than the standard &quot;business&quot; ports (like http, etc.).   <br>  <br> I've called SOE and they inform me that there is no way to reroute patcher and game traffic through another port. <br>  <br> So now I ask the GH Geeks:  is there a way to do client-side network address translation to route game traffic through port 80 or other standard port?  I've thought that the NAT function of a simple firewall/router between the client and the switch might do the trick, as it seems that all I need for the client side is to get the request out to the SOE server.  Of course, there's the other problem of how the SOE server will respond.  Anyone know whether the SOE patch or game servers will accept queries from port 80? <br>  <br> Any thoughts on how I can get reconnected?  I'd really hate to go the dial up route. 
				  </span>
	          </td>
	        </tr>
